snippet.textDisplay:
If you sing this song in the aspect of the person who he speaks of, you'll feel the song a bit more.

I choke up when I do because I deal with depression, anxiety and mood swings. Simple tasks can be difficult to get through,but its pushing yourself beyond it that is an every struggle.

I see children who have lost their parents to suicide and expect myself to be there in the future, but I'm fighting to prevent that. It's hard... even as a person who endures, I fail to be mindful of others ALL the time. Its nobody's fault but my own.
